Saudi Retail Lending Jumps 17% in February, Eqtisadiah Reports

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-04-24T09:13:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-24/saudi-retail-lending-jumps-17-in-february-eqtisadiah-reports.html
Saudi Arabia  reported a 17 percent
jump in retail lending at the end of February,  Al Eqtisadiah 
reported, citing  Saudi Credit Bureau  (SIMAH) Chairman Nabil Al
Mubarak.  The February loan total rose to 230 billion riyals ($61
billion) from 195 billion riyals a year earlier, the newspaper
said, citing Al Mubarak.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  